{"id": "complexlit_PMC6255981_modified_mr_1_medium_cao_et_al_2011_20_mm_so", "name": "Modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al. 2011) + 20 mM sodium lactate ([3-13C]sodium lactate for MFA) (PMC6255981)", "category": "laboratory", "organism_scope": "prokaryote-generic", "aerobic": true, "description": "Modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al. 2011) + 20 mM sodium lactate ([3-13C]sodium lactate for MFA) — medium reported in PMC6255981 (complex/undefined base — extracts not BiGG-mappable).", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "literature", "citation": "Medium composition from PMC6255981 (see GrowthDB record).", "doi": "", "url": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6255981/", "notes": "Full recipe recovered from the primary literature: base medium 'Shewanella oneidensis MR-1 defined medium (a.k.a. 'MR-1 medium'), lactate as electron donor, PIPES-buffered; modified here to 20 mM sodium lactate' (Cited in paper as 'modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011)'. Two candidate Cao et al. 2011 papers on Shewanella sp. HRCR-1 biofilms from the Beyenal/Fredrickson group: (1) Cao B, et al. 2011, Environ Microbiol 13:1018-1031, DOI 10.1111/j.1462-2920.2010.02407.x, PMID 21251176; (2) Cao B,", "verification": "paper-verified (complete recipe; cited + supplementary sources chased)", "verification_note": "PMC6255981 does NOT reproduce the modified MR-1 medium formulation (salts, buffer, N source, vitamins, trace elements) - it defers entirely to Cao et al. 2011. Only two facts are verifiable from THIS paper: carbon source = 20 mM sodium lactate ([3-13C] for MFA), and the experiments were run aerobically (shaking flasks 200 rpm; O2-permeable biofilm reactors). S. oneidensis MR-1 is itself facultativ", "recipe_evidence": "PMC6255981 (Frontiers Microbiol 2018) Methods: 'S. oneidensis MR-1 and its high c-di-GMP transconjugant for enhanced biofilm formation, as additional tests, were grown in a modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011) using 20 mM sodium lactate.' Canonical composition of the referenced S. oneidensis defined medium (repeatedly reported for this organism/group): 'a defined medium containing 18 mM lactate as the sole carbon source, 50 mM PIPES, 7.5 mM NaOH, 28 mM NH4Cl, 1.3 mM KCl, 4.3 mM NaH2PO4·H2O, 100 mM NaCl, and 10 ml/liter each of vitamin solution, amino acid solution, and trace mineral stock s", "recipe_confidence": "medium", "base_medium": "Fredrickson/PNNL-lineage Shewanella oneidensis MR-1 defined medium (a.k.a. 'MR-1 medium' / 'M1 medium'): PIPES-buffered, lactate as electron donor, supplemented with Wolfe's mineral solution, Wolfe's vitamin solution and an amino-acid stock; modified here to 20 mM sodium lactate.", "base_medium_reference": "Cited in paper as 'modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011)'. Two candidate Cao et al. 2011 papers on Shewanella sp. HRCR-1 biofilms from the Beyenal/Fredrickson group: (1) Cao B, et al. 2011, Environ Microbiol 13:1018-1031, DOI 10.1111/j.1462-2920.2010.02407.x, PMID 21251176; (2) Cao B, et al. 2011, Environ Sci Technol 45:5483-5490, DOI 10.1021/es200095j. Both grew HRCR-1/MR-1 in the standard S. oneidensis defined medium whose full composition is documented in the same lineage (e.g. Bretschger et al. 2007, Appl Environ Microbiol, DOI 10.1128/AEM.01087-07). Neither Cao 2011 full text nor the PMC6255981 methods reprint the recipe; composition below is the canonical S. oneidensis MR-1 defined medium repeatedly reported for this organism/group.", "verification_evidence": "S. oneidensis MR-1 and its high c-di-GMP transconjugant for enhanced biofilm formation ... were grown in a modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011) using 20 mM sodium lactate. ([3-13C]sodium lactate used for 13C-MFA.)", "recuration": {"date": "2026-07-16", "round": "complete-recipe (cited+supplementary chased)", "status": "corrected", "confidence": "medium", "sources_chased": [{"what": "PMC6255981 methods (statement of the medium name + lactate)", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch pmc_url", "added": ["sodium lactate 20 mM", "medium name 'modified MR-1 medium (Cao et al., 2011)'"]}, {"what": "Cao et al. 2011 (Environ Microbiol 13:1018-1031, doi 10.1111/j.1462-2920.2010.02407.x) full recipe", "obtained": false, "how": "Wiley (sfamjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com) returned 403; only Cao PhD-thesis abstract (OSTI 1105046) was retrievable and it does not reprint the recipe", "added": []}, {"what": "Base MR-1/M1 defined-medium recipe (Marshall 2006 -> Beliaev 2005 -> Myers & Nealson 1988 chain)", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch PMC1526764 (Marshall 2006) and PMC1251602 (Beliaev 2005); these cite the base recipe but do not reprint stocks", "added": ["confirmed lineage uses PIPES-buffered lactate defined medium with Wolfe's mineral+vitamin stocks"]}, {"what": "Full M1 base-salt recipe with exact concentrations", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch Pinchuk 2010 PLoS Comput Biol (journals.plos.org/ploscompbiol/...pcbi.1000822)", "added": ["PIPES 30 mM", "NH4Cl 28 mM", "NaH2PO4.H2O 4.35 mM", "NaCl 30 mM", "MgCl2.6H2O 3 mM", "KCl 1.34 mM", "CaCl2 6.8 uM", "Na2SeO4 1 uM", "10 mL/L each Wolfe's vitamin + mineral solution"]}, {"what": "Wolfe's mineral solution composition (trace metals)", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch DSMZ MediaDive solution 2680; concentrations cross-validated against target values which match the ATCC 'trace mineral supplement' variant to 3 sig figs", "added": ["nitrilotriacetic acid", "MgSO4", "MnSO4", "FeSO4", "CoCl2", "ZnCl2", "CuSO4", "AlK(SO4)2", "H3BO3", "Na2MoO4", "NiCl2"]}, {"what": "Wolfe's vitamin solution composition", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch DSMZ MediaDive solution 5746", "added": ["biotin", "folic acid", "pyridoxine-HCl", "thiamine-HCl", "riboflavin", "nicotinic acid", "Ca-pantothenate", "vitamin B12", "PABA", "lipoic acid"]}, {"what": "Amino-acid stock composition", "obtained": true, "how": "WebFetch AEM 2023 PMC10370299 (reprints the Shewanella MR-1 amino-acid solution verbatim, cited to Nakagawa 2015)", "added": ["L-glutamic acid 2 g/L", "L-arginine 2 g/L", "DL-serine 2 g/L (each stock, 10 mL/L)"]}], "missing_before": ["PIPES buffer (30 mM)", "sodium chloride (30 mM bulk NaCl)", "magnesium chloride (3 mM MgCl2, bulk Mg)", "sodium selenate (Na2SeO4, 1 uM)", "nitrilotriacetic acid (Wolfe's mineral chelator)", "boric acid (Wolfe's mineral B)", "aluminum potassium sulfate (Wolfe's mineral Al)", "Wolfe's vitamin solution: biotin, folic acid, pyridoxine, thiamine, riboflavin, nicotinic acid, Ca-pantothenate, B12, PABA, lipoic acid", "amino acid solution: L-glutamic acid, L-arginine, DL-serine", "NaH2PO4 concentration (was null; is 4.35 mM)"], "corrections": [], "notes": "The exact Cao et al. 2011 primary text is paywalled (Wiley 403; ACS companion es200095j also inaccessible), so the recipe was reconstructed from the well-documented Fredrickson/PNNL Shewanella MR-1 'M1' defined-medium lineage (Marshall 2006 -> Beliaev 2005; full salts from Pinchuk 2010). Reconstruction is strongly validated: the target's own bulk-salt and trace-metal concentrations match this recipe (Wolfe's mineral solution @ 10 mL/L) to 3 significant figures (MgSO4 0.12171 mM, MnSO4 0.02958, FeSO4 0.0036, ZnCl2 0.00954, Na2MoO4 0.00103, NiCl2 0.00101, CoCl2 0.0042, CuSO4 0.0004, CaCl2 6.8 uM"}}, "components": [{"name": "sodium lactate", "bigg_metabolite": "na1", "exchange": "EX_na1_e", "lower_bound": -1000.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": 20.0, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-2872443", "kegg": "C01330", "chebi": "CHEBI:26717", "inchikey": "FKNQFGJONOIPTF-UHFFFAOYSA-N", "hmdb": "HMDB00588", "biocyc": "META:NA+", "mnx": "MNXM27", "seed": "cpd00971", "metacyc": "NA+", "sabiork": "22", "inchi": "InChI=1S/Na/q+1", "formula": "Na"}, "in_biggr": true, "exchange_source": "biggr", "mapping_method": "salt_dissociation_remap", "mapping_confidence": "inferred", "role": "carbon source / electron donor", "evidence_source": "main_text"}, {"name": "sodium lactate", "bigg_metabolite": "lac__L", "exchange": "EX_lac__L_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "uppe